Experience Improved Performance for Big Objects

To optimize performance, data is no longer encoded or validated during the write process when itâ€™s larger than the maximum allowed size. When data is read, the UI layer interprets precision and scale as specified in the metadata. Previously, precision and scale were enforced when writing data to or reading data from a big object.

Where: This change applies to Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer editions.

When: This feature rolls out in May 2024.
